{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566546","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566546"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:43:39+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:43:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18841"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18841","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18841"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.01,0.88,0.01,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11574"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79651"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11574","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11574"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18841"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64956"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11298"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27240"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27241"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79651","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79651"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student observes different approaches to patient care during clinical rotations. They notice that healthcare outcomes appear to be influenced by the professional conduct of medical practitioners.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary importance of medical professionalism?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Ensures compliance with hospital policies","Reduces administrative workload","Maintains public trust and improves patient outcomes","Promotes career advancement opportunities","Prevents legal complaints against practitioners"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that professionalism \u003Cstrong\u003Emaintains public trust and improves patient outcomes\u003C/strong\u003E. Professional behaviour creates an environment of trust, respect, and effective communication that directly enhances the quality of patient care and health outcomes. When patients trust their healthcare providers, they are more likely to disclose important information, adhere to treatment plans, and actively participate in their care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevents legal complaints against practitioners\u003C/strong\u003E - While professionalism may reduce the risk of complaints, this is a secondary benefit rather than its primary importance\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEnsures compliance with hospital policies\u003C/strong\u003E - Compliance is just one aspect of professionalism, not its fundamental purpose\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPromotes career advancement opportunities\u003C/strong\u003E - Career advancement is a potential consequence of professional behaviour but not its primary importance\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduces administrative workload\u003C/strong\u003E - This is not a key purpose of professional behaviour and may not always be true\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMedical professionalism is fundamental to the practice of medicine because it establishes the ethical framework and behavioural standards necessary for effective healthcare delivery. It encompasses commitment to patient welfare, maintenance of clinical competence, honesty with patients, appropriate relationships with colleagues, and dedication to quality improvement.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Medical professionalism encompasses core values including integrity, accountability, respect, and commitment to patient welfare above self-interest.","Professional behaviour directly impacts patient trust, healthcare outcomes, and the effectiveness of healthcare delivery.","Maintaining professional standards is essential for both individual patient care and public confidence in the medical profession."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Morreale MK, Balon R, Louie AK, Guerrero APS, Aggarwal R, Coverdale J, Beresin EV, Brenner AM. The Vital Importance of Professionalism in Medical Education. Acad Psychiatry. 2023 Aug;47(4):340-343. doi: 10.1007/s40596-023-01840-3. Erratum in: Acad Psychiatry. 2023 Oct;47(5):574. doi: 10.1007/s40596-023-01864-9. PMID: 37548858. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37548858/","Forouzadeh M, Kiani M, Bazmi S. Professionalism and its role in the formation of medical professional identity. Med J Islam Repub Iran. 2018 Dec 26;32:130. doi: 10.14196/mjiri.32.130. PMID: 30815425; PMCID: PMC6387805. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37548858/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64956"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18841"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64956","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64956"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-15T12:21:24+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-15T12:21:56+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11574"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79651"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://a